name: Vitamin A, RAE
Notes: retinol activity equivalents - this is what RDA's are based on.

name: Carotene, beta
Notes: provitamin A - meaning it can be transformed into vitamin A by the body.

name: Carotene, alpha
Notes: probably also provitamin A - meaning it can be transformed into vitamin A by the body.

name: Vitamin D2 (ergocalciferol)
Notes: one form of vitamin D => ignore it.

name: Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol)
Notes: one form of vitamin D => ignore it.

name: 25-hydroxycholecalciferol
Notes: prehormone that is changed into vitamin D => ignore it.

name: Vitamin D (D2 + D3)
Notes: All vitamin D forms => include it.
